<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAITI POOR IN EMBARGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Haiti Poor Get Poorer in Embargo" (May 23) needs to be absorbed by our 
politicians. How can we expect the people of Haiti and Iraq (against whom we 
also have an embargo) to rise up against their dictators when their countries 
are in chaos? People are too weak and sickly to do anything against their 
governments while those in government don't seem to be suffering any adverse 
effects.It seems to me that we are actually helping the dictators to stay in 
power. We say we allow food and medicine into the countries but the poor are 
not getting either because they have no money. 
</P>
<P>
 We are causing vast numbers of people to suffer miserably. We've got to find a 
more effective way to deal with these cruel regimes. Allowing babies and their 
parents to suffer and to die is surely not the American way. 
</P>
<P>
 SISTER MARY SEVILLA 
</P>
<P>
 Lakewood 
