<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION ROUNDUP; HAESSIG HITS THREE HOME RUNS, LEADS LAS VIRGENES' 13-4 
ROMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Center fielder Bhret Haessig hit three home runs Wednesday to lead Las 
Virgenes to a 13-4 victory over Granada Hills West in a District 20 game at 
Calabasas High. 
</P>
<P>
 Haessig was four for four and drove in six runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Sass homered, went three for four and added four RBIs for Las Virgenes 
(2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank South 2, Sunland Tujunga 0 -- Right-hander Mike Bassett (1-1) pitched 
a three-hitter, striking out four and walking one. Losing pitcher Newt Wimer 
threw a four-hitter but two of his walks led to Burbank South's runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley North 9, Woodland Hills East 5 -- Brandon Murphy's two-run single in 
the eighth inning triggered a four-run rally and gave Valley North (1-0) the 
victory at Taft High. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony Ardito and Tony Montiel also had run-scoring singles in the inning. 
Montiel was three for four with four runs batted in. Murphy was three for five 
with two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 15, Burbank North 5 -- Van Nuys South drew 15 walks in a District 20 
game at Grant High. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Levine was two for three, including a single and a double, and drove in 
two runs. Mike Weiss was two for two. Rudy Velasquez was one for two with three 
RBIs. Tommy Smith had a three-run double in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Sepulveda 17, Mission Hills 16 -- The teams combined for 16 extra-base hits at 
Alemany High. Doug Segraves was four for six and drove in two runs for Mission 
Hills (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills 7, North Hollywood 2 -- After Verdugo Hills starter Danny 
Fernandez had to leave the game with a sore arm in the second inning, Phil 
Onsaga pitched five scoreless innings, allowing two hits and striking out 
seven. Bryan Chan hit a home run and scored three times. David Boger was three 
for four with three RBIs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
