<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: AREA PAIR TO PLAY IN STATE SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley High third baseman Ryan Hankins and Notre Dame pitcher Rich Igou 
have been selected to play in the state North-South all-star baseball series 
this weekend in Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty players from Southern California, chosen from a tryout Sunday, will 
face a team from the North in games Friday, Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hankins, Marmonte League co-player of the year, hit nine home runs for the 
Pioneers this season. He has signed to play at UNLV and was drafted by the 
Philadelphia Phillies in the 33rd round last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Igou won 11 games and hit six home runs for Notre Dame, winning Mission League 
most valuable player honors. Igou has signed with the University of San 
Francisco and was drafted by the Kansas City Royals in an undisclosed round. 
JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
