<TEXT>
<P>
 USC first baseman J.P. Roberge has signed with the Dodgers after being drafted 
in the 18th round last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Roberge, who went to St. Francis High, batted .332 with 11 home runs, 48 runs 
batted in and 18 stolen bases as a junior this spring. He will either be 
assigned to the Dodgers' Rookie League team in Great Falls, Mont. or their 
Class A affiliate in Yakima, Wash. DANA HADDAD 
