<HEADLINE>
<P>
LINDENBERG LEADS NORTH TO SOFTBALL VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon's Nina Lindenberg scored two runs and drove in two more to lead the 
North a 7-0 victory over the South in the third Orange County North-South 
all-star softball game Wednesday at Brea-Olinda High. 
</P>
<P>
 Lindenberg scored the only run the North needed in the first inning against El 
Toro's Misty Lauby. 
</P>
<P>
 After a two-out walk, Lindenberg stole second and scored on a single by 
Cypress' Christa Saindon. Lindenberg also keyed the North's five-run third 
inning. Lauby surrendered six runs despite giving up only two hits in three 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 The South committed three errors in the third and three times allowed runners 
to reach base by failing to throw out the lead runner. 
</P>
<P>
 An error and two fielder's choices loaded the bases, and Lindenberg singled up 
the middle, scoring Los Alamitos' Debbie Wilson (two runs batted in) and 
Rosary's Nicola Walsh, whose slide allowed her to elude the catcher's tag. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge's Alison Johnsen had three of the South's four hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson, Rancho Alamitos' Jill Otto and El Dorado's Heather Hamer combined for 
the shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 North All-Stars 7, South All-Stars 0 
</P>
<P>
 North: 105- 010-0 -- 7-5- 0 
</P>
<P>
 South: 000- 000-0 -- 0-4- 3 
</P>
<P>
 D. Wilson, Otto (4), Hamer (7) and C. Wilson, Al-Moradi (7). Lauby, Godwin 
(4), Noffsinger (7) and Kirk, Willson (5). W -- D. Wilson. L -- Lauby. MARTIN 
HENDERSON 
