<TEXT>
<P>
 Cruttenden & Co., the Irvine brokerage and investment bank, said it has hired 
four new senior managers. 
</P>
<P>
 Will Porter, a former Cruttenden employee who left to join the Irvine 
brokerage L.H. Friend, will return as director of trading for institutional 
markets.Rick Sample, formerly of Related Capital Co. of Rancho Santa Margarita, 
will join Cruttenden as retail branch manager, replacing Brad Weddon. 
</P>
