<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; POLICE 
ARREST SUSPECT IN 15 KIDNAPINGS, RAPES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was arrested Wednesday on suspicion of kidnaping and raping 15 women in 
the Wilshire and Hollywood areas over the past four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean Patrick Mitchell, 33, of Los Angeles, allegedly began his crime rampage 
by kidnaping lone women coming out of restaurants. More recently, he allegedly 
began kidnaping and sexually assaulting women in pairs, said Los Angeles Police 
Lt. Ross Moen.  
</P>
<P>
 Most of the victims were white brunettes in their early 20s who were abducted 
while leaving restaurants, then robbed and raped, Moen said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bail was set at $2.5 million. 
