<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: TORRANCE; MAN CONVICTED 
IN SLAYING OF CATERING TRUCK OWNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Monica man who said he was hired by a caterer to intimidate the 
competition was convicted of murdering a catering truck owner after an argument 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Cornell Price was found guilty this week of second-degree murder in the May 
13, 1993, shooting of Jose Argueta outside a lumber yard. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said Price threw Argueta against a coffee maker in his truck and 
told him to leave the city. When Argueta motioned toward a gun, Price disarmed 
him, shot him in the leg, threw him out of the truck and shot him in the back, 
prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Price's attorney said the shooting was self defense. 
</P>
<P>
 Sentencing was scheduled for June 28. 
</P>
