<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; EDUCATION: LMU STUDENT WINS GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dennis Metro, a senior history major at Loyola Marymount University in 
Westchester, has been awarded a National Security Education Undergraduate 
Scholarship Program grant to study in Hungary. 
</P>
<P>
 Metro, 22, received the grant from the Institute of International Education. 
He will attend political science and Russian and Hungarian language classes at 
Janus Pannonius Tudomanyos Egyetem, a university in Pecs, Hungary, during the 
1994-95 academic year. 
</P>
<P>
 The program was created to help Americans better understand foreign cultures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
