<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; ART: EXHIBIT WILL EXPLORE PATRIOTISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Creative interpretations of patriotism and the meaning of America will be on 
display in "Stars & Stripes: An Exhibition of the American Flag" at the Pacific 
Design Center's Murray Feldman Gallery beginning June 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Hundreds of objects will show interpretations of the flag's design and meaning 
as well as its relationship to art, politics and history. Displays include a 
can of Old Glory-brand asparagus, a flag made from more than 2,800 red, white 
and blue pencils and an 1865 hand-stitched wool flag banner. 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibit ends July 30. The Pacific Design Center is at 8687 Melrose Ave., 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
