<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; MUSEUM: MODELS NEEDED FOR DISPLAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Petersen Automotive Museum, which opens Saturday on the Miracle Mile, is 
seeking people to serve as models for wax mannequins to be used in displays -- 
people, that is, who can make a $20,000 donation. 
</P>
<P>
 The mannequins will depict such figures as 1930s car salesmen, 1920s gas 
station attendants and chauffeurs for Hollywood stars. 
</P>
<P>
 No experience is required. The donation is tax-deductible. 
</P>
<P>
 The $40-million, 300,000-square-foot museum chronicles the evolution of Los 
Angeles car culture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
