<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: TORRANCE; TEACHERS SEEK RAISES AND BETTER BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teachers here will seek an 8.8% salary increase for the 1994-95 school year, 
union officials said this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The Torrance Teachers Assn. also will ask for changes in health care, dental, 
vision and life insurance benefits, said spokesman Bill Franchini. 
</P>
<P>
 The group's goal is to reduce employees' out-of-pocket expenses, which have 
continued to rise although the district's contribution to those costs has not 
changed since 1991, Franchini said. 
</P>
<P>
 Franchini presented the plan at Monday's school board meeting. The board will 
hold a public hearing on the matter July 5. 
</P>
<P>
 After members of the board have an opportunity to comment, the district's 
negotiators will meet with teachers union representatives. MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</TEXT>
