<HEADLINE>
<P>
SILENT FILM 'PHANTOM' AT AVALON BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Phantom of the Opera" comes to Santa Catalina Island on Saturday.  
</P>
<P>
 The 1925 silent film will be shown during the island's annual Silent Film 
Benefit in the newly renovated Art Deco Avalon Theater.Located on the first 
floor of the island's Casino Building, the 1,184-seat theater was built in 
1929. 
</P>
<P>
 All proceeds benefit the Catalina Island Museum Society. 
</P>
<P>
 "There is a lot of audience participation in watching a silent film," said 
Patricia Moore, director of the Catalina Museum. "It's fun for viewers of all 
ages, and people are always amazed at the sophistication of the art of silent 
film." 
</P>
<P>
 The film, which stars Lon Chaney, will be accompanied by Gaylord Carter on the 
theater's original 1929 Page organ. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $7 for adults and $5 for museum members, children under 12 and 
members of groups of 20 or more. Information: (310) 510-1520. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
