<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MALIBU; MAN PLEADS NOT GUILTY TO CHARGE OF SEX WITH GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 49-year-old Malibu man has pleaded not guilty to charges that he committed 
and photographed sex acts with a minor. 
</P>
<P>
 Ronald Bruce Sindoni, a producer for Malibu's cable television public access 
channel, faces arraignment June 16 in West Los Angeles Municipal Court on 
charges including statutory rape, oral copulation and having a minor pose for a 
photo in a lewd and lascivious manner.He is being held in lieu of $210,000 
bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors filed charges against Sindoni two weeks ago after employees at a 
Venice one-hour photo store gave the photographs to police. Police questioned 
him at the store and arrested him later when it was determined the girl in the 
pictures was 15 years old. 
</P>
<P>
 During testimony at a preliminary hearing Monday, the girl said she met 
Sindoni in January at KBU-TV, a nonprofit television production company that 
tapes City Council meetings and events for cable Channel 15. She said she and 
Sindoni began a consensual sexual relationship while she worked at the 
production company learning film editing and that the photographs were taken 
with her consent. 
</P>
<P>
 In a statement to the judge, Sindoni accused the court of violating the 
minor's constitutional rights "to eat, act and be who she wants to be." 
KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
