<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST LOS ANGELES; 2 KILLED IN SEPARATE SHOOTINGS ON STREETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police continued investigations Wednesday into two separate fatal shootings on 
the Westside this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Corey Payton, 24, was killed in an alley in Cheviot Hills about 10:30 p.m. 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the South-Central resident was last seen talking to friends in the 
6000 block of Sawyer Avenue moments before being shot. 
</P>
<P>
 "Local residents heard gunshots and ran out to find Mr. Payton lying in the 
alley," said Los Angeles Police Detective Frank Bolan. Payton was taken to 
Kaiser-West Los Angeles Hospital, where he died about 11 p.m. from multiple 
gunshot wounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not determined a motive for the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6:15 a.m. Saturday, Michael Anthony Tucker was slain at Smiley Avenue and 
Hauser Boulevard in West Los Angeles, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tucker had argued briefly with two men, one of whom pulled a handgun and shot 
him several times in the head and chest, killing him instantly, said Bernard 
Rogers, an LAPD detective. 
</P>
