<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIKE PATH: LETTING WALKERS AND BICYCLISTS SHARE THE SCENIC ROUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 21.6 miles of bike path featured in the May 19 Westside section is exactly 
the same 14-foot width from Pacific Palisades to Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1.5-mile segment in Pacific Palisades, however, has a designated walker 
path included in that width. Then, the walker portion is arbitrarily painted 
away and the bike path is suddenly expanded. I have often wondered why this is 
so. 
</P>
<P>
 Why not extend the walker portion for the full length of the path? Then 
everyone would travel single file in peace and order. 
</P>
<P>
 FRANCES SPIELBERG 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades  
</P>
</TEXT>
