<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA: PROS AND CONS OF NEW WESTSIDE FORMAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My husband and I applaud the new Westside format. We find increased in-depth 
coverage of Westside issues, events and individuals.The cover photographs lead 
us into the centerfold feature story, which now receives more column space. We 
now think of Westside as a local, twice-weekly magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 CHRISTINE SWANSON 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Why fix (it) if it ain't broke? Your new Westside (section) is AWFUL. (It's) 
hard to find the things about the Westside one likes to read. It looks like a 
small-town news sheet. Your old format was quite interesting. 
</P>
<P>
 FINI LITTLEJOHN 
</P>
<P>
 Malibu  
</P>
</TEXT>
