WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CHATSWORTH; OPEN HOUSE TO COVER EARTHQUAKE ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIO MORAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Earthquake Service Center in Chatsworth will hold an open house featuring 
a series of seminars on earthquake preparedness and other topics Saturday from 
10 a.m. to 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, at 20525 Nordhoff St., is operated jointly by the Governor's 
Office of Emergency Services and the Federal Emergency Management Agency.It is 
designed to provide long-term local, state and federal assistance and 
information to individuals and businesses. Crisis counseling and tax advisers 
on disaster-related issues are also available at the center. The center -- and 
nine others throughout the area -- are still accepting applications for aid. 
The deadline is July 18. JULIO MORAN 
