<P>
 A 42-year-old Port Hueneme man convicted of engaging in sex acts with a 
6-year-old boy is mentally disabled and should not be sent to prison, a jury 
ruled Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Superior Court Judge Lawrence Storch promptly ordered Dennis Ray Thompson 
remanded to the California Department of Mental Health for placement in a state 
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's not going to be out" for a long time, Deputy Dist. Atty. Patrice D. 
Koenig said after the sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
 The same jury convicted Thompson -- who has brain damage and suffers from a 
severe speech impediment -- of five counts of child molestation, Koenig said. 
</P>
