<P>
 Small business owners in Simi Valley in need of a financial boost to help 
repair damage caused by the Jan. 17 earthquake may be eligible for loans from 
the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Owners of businesses with up to 20 employees are invited to apply for 
short-term loans of up to $2,500 out of a special fund the city has created 
with money from a federal Community Development Block Grant. 
