EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; SCHOOLS ALLOWED TO ESTABLISH DRESS 
CODES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley school officials have agreed to let individual schools establish 
dress codes that encourage, but don't require, students to wear uniforms. 
</P>
<P>
 Three of five members of the Simi Valley Unified school board said Tuesday 
that they believe schools should be allowed to establish voluntary uniform 
policies if parents and staff support the idea. 
</P>
<P>
 The decision opens the way for Garden Grove Elementary to move forward with a 
policy that would encourage students to wear blue pants and navy skirts with 
white blouses or shirts. Students not wearing the uniform would be subject to a 
strict dress code, said Principal Elroy Peterson. 
</P>
<P>
 Board President Carla Kurachi and members Judy Barry and Doug Crosse supported 
allowing schools to introduce uniforms, while board members Diane Collins and 
Debbie Sandland were opposed. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
