<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Beastie Boys' "Ill Communication" album will top the national pop charts 
when Billboard magazine hits the stands Saturday. The new punk rap collection 
sold an estimated 220,000 copies during its first week in the stores. A distant 
second: Ace of Base's "The Sign." 
</P>
</TEXT>
