<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; BODY OF SLAIN MAN FOUND IN APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The body of a 23-year-old man who had been shot to death was discovered in his 
apartment Wednesday just after midnight. It was found by a friend who broke 
into the apartment because he was worried at not having seen the victim for 
several days. 
</P>
<P>
 Police identified the victim as Arash Nakhjavani, who had been shot in the 
head and torso. They said he may have been dead for several days. 
</P>
<P>
 Shawn Curran, a neighbor in the apartment building in the 25000 block of Cross 
Creek Drive, said, "We hadn't seen him (Nakhjavani) in a few days but just 
thought maybe he was out of town. We were sleeping and all of a sudden we heard 
his buddy screaming, 'He's dead!' " 
</P>
<P>
 Police Sgt. Ed McDonald said there did not appear to have been an earlier 
forced entry and that robbery probably wasn't involved in the slaying because 
valuables had not been taken from the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's possible that he knew the person who shot him but we don't know for 
sure," McDonald said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they had yet to uncover any suspects. An autopsy was to have been 
performed Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
 Nakhjavani moved into the apartment about a month ago and had not been 
involved in any problems, according to his neighbor. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was a young guy on his own," Curran said. "He was a nice guy -- the kind 
of neighbor who would say hello and ask how you're doing. He had invited me 
over for a beer but I never made it over there." 
</P>
<P>
 Police and residents said violence is uncommon in the sprawling, 
Mediterranean-style apartment complex on the eastern edge of the city. 
</P>
<P>
 "When you live in a neighborhood like this, you don't expect these kinds of 
things to happen," Curran said. "That's why you pay the money, so you feel 
relaxed and safe." 
</P>
<P>
 Nakhjavani's death is the first homicide in Yorba Linda in 1994. The city had 
one homicide last year, McDonald said.GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
