<TEXT>
<P>
 Starving for some new tunes? 
</P>
<P>
 Pop on down to a Moby Disk Records store with a can of food, and they might 
just have the cure for your auditory pangs. 
</P>
<P>
 "Feed the hungry while you feed your ears" is Moby Disks' campaign to combat 
hunger, a two-week food drive ending June 19. The drive works like this: 
music-hungry customers bring in a canned food product, and in return they 
receive a $1 to $5 discount on any CD in the store. The chain has stores in 
Canoga Park and Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 All canned goods collected will be donated to the Los Angeles Regional 
Foodbank, which will in turn distribute the food to charities that feed the 
needy throughout Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 "The hungry are not as glorified as AIDS and earthquakes," said marketing 
director Tracy Brophy. MAKI BECKER 
