<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; BULLOCK'S REOPENS 2 FLOORS FOR BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For Bullock's shoppers, today is the day to see the glass half full. 
</P>
<P>
 The first two of the four floors in the earthquake-battered Bullock's Sherman 
Oaks will reopen today, marking the completion of all structural work to the 
building.The department store is located in the Sherman Oaks Fashion Square, 
14000 Riverside Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The 309,600-square-foot store, with four selling floors, has been closed since 
Jan. 17 because of damage from the 6.8 Northridge earthquake. Repairs included 
replacing interior floors, a new exterior facade, main entrance, lighting and 
building signage. 
</P>
<P>
 Following more repairs, the third floor is expected to reopen July 15 and the 
fourth floor will be reopened mid-October. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours for the Sherman Oaks store will be 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. Monday through 
Friday; 10 a.m. to 7 p.m. Saturday, and 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The store had been operating its women's ready-to-wear and accessories 
business out of the 40,000-square-foot store formally occupied by I. Magnin. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokeswoman for Macy's West/Bullock's said she has no estimates for repair 
costs. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
