<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARRIS SAYS HE WILL KEEP LAKERS' STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Laker Coach Del Harris said Wednesday that he will retain assistants Bill 
Bertka, Michael Cooper and Larry Drew on the staff for next season. 
</P>
<P>
 All worked for former coach Magic Johnson, and Bertka and Drew were on the 
staff of Randy Pfund, who was fired last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Bertka will enter his 14th season as a Laker assistant and has 22 seasons as 
an assistant in the NBA. No active assistant has been around longer in that 
role. 
</P>
<P>
 Cooper joined the staff when Johnson was named to replace Pfund. 
</P>
<P>
 Drew spent 10 seasons as an NBA player and has two seasons as an assistant 
coach. 
</P>
