<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; WERNER IS SET TO SELL PADRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSS NEWHAN and BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tom Werner, chairman of the San Diego Padres, has reached a tentative 
agreement to sell the team to Malcolm I. Glazer for $82.5 million, sources told 
The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Glazer is CEO of First Allied Corp. of Boynton Beach, Fla., a financial 
institution with investments in real estate and TV stations.His agreement with 
Werner hinges on the approval of other owners, a process believed to have 
started informally. 
</P>
<P>
 Werner was attending an owners meeting in Cincinnati on Wednesday and could 
not be reached. It is uncertain if he is simply reducing his majority ownership 
or leaving the club entirely. Glazer, who intends to keep the club in San 
Diego, a requisite of his approval, is believed to be buying out all of 
Werner's 14 partners, sources said. 
</P>
<P>
 Werner bought the club in 1990 from Joan Kroc. The reported price was $75 
million. ROSS NEWHAN and BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
