<HEADLINE>
<P>
WINDMILLER NAMED CSUN'S SOFTBALL MVP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All-American Amy Windmiller was named most valuable player of the Cal State 
Northridge softball team by a vote of her teammates.Windmiller (26-2) led the 
nation with a 0.36 earned-run average. The senior right-hander had 202 
strikeouts in 194 innings and walked only 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Third baseman Shannon Jones, who paced the Matadors with a .409 batting 
average, 17 doubles, 13 home runs and 56 runs batted in, was named most 
outstanding offensive player. She set school records for home runs and RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortstop Vicky Rios, who had a .945 fielding average, was honored as best 
defensive and most inspirational player. 
</P>
<P>
 Catcher Jennifer Parker was named most improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
