<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Northrop Grumman Picks New B-2 Head: The aerospace concern named Ralph D. 
Crosby Jr. general manager of its B-2 bomber division, and it announced new 
managers for three of the four divisions created by Northrop's recent purchase 
of Grumman. Crosby, 46, succeeds Oliver C. Boileau, who was previously named 
president of the Grumman subsidiary.The company said John E. Harrison, 58, was 
named general manager of its electronics and systems integration division; 
Wallace C. Solberg, 63, will head its military aircraft unit, and Gerald H. 
Sandler, 59, was named general manager of data systems and services. Management 
of its commercial aircraft division will be announced later this year. The 
Senate Armed Services Committee appears headed toward providing $150 million to 
support the B-2 program beyond production of the currently authorized 20 
aircraft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
