<P>
 Intel, Hewlett-Packard to Join Forces: Continuing a computer-industry 
collaboration trend, the Silicon Valley companies said they will team up to 
develop chips for powerful workstations and servers. Terms of the agreement 
were not disclosed. Systems using the jointly developed technologies will be 
available at the end of the decade, the companies said. 
