<P>
 Vietnam May Market Gas From Oil Wells: The government has appointed a 
consortium of foreign companies to study the feasibility of a $400-million 
project to launch a potentially sizable offshore gas industry, officials said. 
British Gas, Japan's Mitsui & Co. and TransCanada PipeLines have won exclusive 
rights, in partnership with the state oil firm PetroVietnam, to conduct the 
study on opening the gas market. If accepted, they would form a joint venture 
to begin the first major project using gas -- currently being burned off -- 
from oil wells at the Bach Ho (White Tiger) field in the South China Sea, 
Vietnam's only field pumping crude. 
