<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES / ANNE MICHAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By The Goal: Getting to Know Members of Sweden's Soccer Team and ANNE MICHAUD, 
Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Soccer fans will have a chance to meet the Swedish World Cup soccer team in a 
dinner at Gustaf Anders restaurant on June 16. The team plays its first game of 
the series on June 19 against Cameroon, at the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 The dinner, which was arranged through the Consulate General of Sweden, is $75 
a person, tax and tip included. Proceeds benefit the Swedish-American Chamber 
of Commerce, based in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Guests will dine on a smorgasbord of Scandinavian specialties, including whole 
poached salmon, pickled herring, Swedish meatballs and more. Autographed World 
Cup soccer balls will be given away as door prizes. 
</P>
<P>
 1651 Sunflower Ave., South Coast Plaza Village, Santa Ana. (714) 668-1737. 
</P>
